SIMPLE: impure
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impure
<hw>Im*pure"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impurus</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>purus</ets> pure:
cf. F. <ets>impur</ets>. See <er>Pure</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not pure; not clean; dirty; foul; filthy; containing
something which is unclean or unwholesome; mixed or impregnated
extraneous substances; adulterated; <as>as, <ex>impure</ex> water or
air; <ex>impure</ex> drugs, food, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Defiled by sin or guilt; unholy; unhallowed; -- said
of persons or things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Unchaste; lewd; unclean; obscene; <as>as,
<ex>impure</ex> language or ideas</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Impure</xex>
desires.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Script.)</fld> <def>Not purified according to the
ceremonial law of Moses; unclean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Language)</fld> <def>Not accurate; not idiomatic;
<as>as, <ex>impure</ex> Latin; an <ex>impure</ex> style.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impure</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Impure
<hw>Im*pure"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To defile; to pollute.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impurely</ent>⟦br⟧
